	<h3>Side effects of milk </h3>
<p>Though milk's benefits outweigh its disadvantages, there is no denying that milk isn't for everyone. Some people can't digest lactose in milk and hence are lactose intolerant. People who are lactose intolerant can't usually have other dairy products, too, such as yogurt, cheese, and paneer. For others, milk may affect skin leading to acne and exacerbate their eczema. </p>

<p>But if you love milk and just can't give it up, then fear not. There are plenty of milk alternatives that taste pretty good. Some popular alternatives available are soy milk, almond milk, oat milk, coconut milk, cashew milk, rice milk, etc. However, before buying milk alternatives, make sure to read product labels for any added sugar or artificial sweeteners. </p>

				<h3>Final Thoughts</h3>
<p>Milk is one of the most nutrient-rich food out there. It's packed with protein and calcium, which help in bone and teeth development. Shockingly it may also help lose or maintain your weight as it keeps you full for longer. And an increasing number of people are intolerant towards and drink milk alternatives. </p>


